  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Following post-market feedback, the device labelling was updated in Q3 2025 to include a paediatric low-body-weight subgroup (8–20 kg) operating at reduced flow rates (0.4–1.2 L/min), extending the originally validated adult operating envelope (2.0–6.0 L/min). The credibility assessment team determined that the existing validation campaign, conducted in 2023 against adult flow conditions, provides sufficient coverage of the expanded envelope on the basis that the governing non-dimensional shear-stress parameters overlap at the lower end of the adult range. No new experimental validation runs targeting the paediatric sub-range have been conducted, and no updated ValidationResult linking paediatric test points is included in this package.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
