      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes published benchmark cases for rotating-frame turbulent flow at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent MRF rotating-frame solver verified against FDA nozzle benchmark and Taylor-Couette analytical solutions. Results within accepted tolerance bands."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI < 5% for wall-shear-stress and hemolysis-index quantities of interest.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation across three mesh densities yielded GCI below 2.1% for all QoIs at adult operating conditions. Mesh parameters are identical for all production runs. The team asserts the same mesh density is adequate for the paediatric sub-range because the characteristic gap Reynolds numbers remain within the validated adult range at the lower flow boundary; however, no dedicated mesh convergence study at sub-1.2 L/min conditions has been performed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) match simulation inputs within ±5%.",
      "rationale": "Flow loop measurements confirmed inlet flow rate within ±2%, impeller speed within ±0.5%, and blood-analogue viscosity within ±3% of CFD boundary conditions for all five adult test points. Paediatric-range boundary conditions have not been independently measured; the team extrapolates from adult fluid property characterisation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalised index of hemolysis within ±15% of experimental values across all assessed operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD predictions agreed within ±12% of experimental hemolysis index measurements at all five adult operating points (2.0–6.0 L/min). No experimental output comparison exists for the paediatric sub-range (0.4–1.2 L/min); the team considers the adult agreement sufficient to infer coverage of the paediatric envelope by similarity arguments."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (normalised index of hemolysis, volume-averaged scalar stress) directly correspond to the clinical endpoint (RH < 1) for both adult and paediatric patient populations.",
      "rationale": "Normalised index of hemolysis and volume-averaged scalar stress are established QoIs for pump-induced hemolysis per ASTM F1841. These are clinically relevant for the adult population. For the newly added paediatric sub-group, the same QoIs are used; no separate sensitivity analysis has been conducted to confirm that scalar stress thresholds derived from adult erythrocyte fragility data apply equally to paediatric patients, whose red blood cell mechanical properties may differ."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities span the full operating envelope defined in the COU, including all indicated patient populations and flow regimes.",
      "rationale": "The 2023 validation campaign covered five adult operating points spanning 2.0–6.0 L/min, which constitutes the original COU operating envelope. The Q3 2025 label update extended the COU to include a paediatric sub-range of 0.4–1.2 L/min. The credibility assessment team judged that the lower boundary of the adult validation range (2.0 L/min) provides adequate proximity to the upper boundary of the paediatric range (1.2 L/min), and that non-dimensional shear-stress similarity supports extrapolation. No new validation activities targeting the paediatric sub-range have been initiated, and no ValidationResult covering paediatric flow conditions is linked to this package."
    },
